HEADWORD: Quassin
<hw>Quas"sin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>quassine</ets>. See <er>Quassia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The bitter principle of quassia, extracted as a white crystalline
substance; -- formerly called <altname>quassite</altname>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>quass⟦imac⟧in</asp>, and
<asp>quassine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

